{
  "answer": "**Chapter 11 of the *Kātyāyana Smṛti* is on \"The Representative\" (*pratinidhi*), addressing rules for appointing representatives (e.g., by plaintiff or defendant) in legal proceedings, who bears fines or victory/defeat, exemptions for certain relations, and prohibitions in grave cases like killing a Brahmin, theft, adultery, violence, forgery, or treason against the king (where the accused must appear personally).**[^1][^2]\n\n[^1]: *Kātyāyana Smṛti*, ch.11 (work wiki chapter map). [Chapter 11](https://falsafa.corpus/works/unknown-katyayana-smrti-1e06d2/11/translation/)\n\n[^2]: *Kātyāyana Smṛti*, ch.11, ¶1–8 (pars. [p-08b47b], [p-72c190], [p-f2c97e], [p-43d1dd], [p-1d0f85], [p-a0b028], [p-4fc7cc], [p-3b2466]). [Chapter 11](https://falsafa.corpus/works/unknown-katyayana-smrti-1e06d2/11/translation/)",
